Stir together 1/2 cup tomato sauce, pepperoni, oregano and pepper flakes in medium bowl. Add beef; mix together and shape mixture into 4 patties, about 1/2-inch thick. Heat large skillet over medium-high heat. Add patties; cook 5 minutes on each side or until cooked through (160 degrees F). Top each with 1 slice cheese; melt slightly. Remove from heat. Spread 1 tablespoon tomato sauce on bottom half of each bun. Top each with a patty. Spoon remaining tomato sauce evenly over patties. Close with tops of buns. Serve immediately.